Technical UI Implementation Spec for Cursor

Elemental Document Collection Overview Page

Objective

Refactor the Overview tab into a structured executive briefing page for a document collection in Elemental.

This page must support a live demo where the presenter explains that Elemental:
	•	ingested 5 uploaded PDFs
	•	automatically classified the documents
	•	synthesized the deal structure
	•	extracted entities, relationships, agreements, and events
	•	generated a coherent AI narrative
	•	created a launch point into Graph, Timeline, Agreements, Insights, Validation, and Enrichment

The page should no longer feel like a sparse admin dashboard with empty cards.

⸻

1. Implementation goals

Primary goals
	•	Replace weak empty-state blocks with structured summary components
	•	Improve information hierarchy and visual density
	•	Make the Overview page useful in both demo mode and real product use
	•	Support three states cleanly:
	•	ingested but not analyzed
	•	analysis complete
	•	partial extraction

Non-goals
	•	Do not redesign the global top navigation
	•	Do not invent entirely new backend APIs unless necessary
	•	Do not introduce a new design language that clashes with the current Lovelace product styling

⸻

