5. Derived state logic

Create helper functions for state, not inline conditionals everywhere.

Example helpers

const isAnalysisComplete = collection.status === "complete";
const isAnalysisPending = collection.status === "not_started" || collection.status === "processing";
const isPartial = collection.status === "partial";

Add helpers for CTA labels

function getPrimaryActionLabel(status: CollectionOverviewData["status"]) {
  if (status === "not_started") return "Run Initial Analysis";
  if (status === "processing") return "Analysis Running";
  return "View Graph";
}


⸻

6. Empty and partial states

Do not render giant empty analytics panels

Instead:

If analysis is pending
	•	show header
	•	show source docs
	•	show collection health
	•	show placeholders for deal summary, narrative, stats

Placeholder pattern

Use a proper placeholder card:
	•	title stays visible
	•	body explains what the module will show
	•	primary CTA appears if relevant

Example placeholder copy

“Run initial analysis to generate a synthesized deal summary, identify entities and agreements, and create a cited graph from this document collection.”

If extraction is partial

Render available data and label incomplete modules as:
	•	Partial
	•	Needs review
	•	Still processing

Do not show “0 entities” if the system simply has not finished.

