Implementation note: BNY retrieval reference

Use `import/BNY-README.md` as a reconstruction and retrieval reference, not as a canonical full entity directory.

What it does provide
	•	An MCP-based recipe for loading the BNY graph from the 5 document seeds
	•	The core traversal pattern for building an entity table keyed by NEID
	•	Specific named examples with NEIDs, including document seeds, event hubs, and key property-bearing entities

What it does not provide
	•	A complete final list of every entity name and its NEID

Implementation consequence
	•	If the UI needs a full entity directory, derive it from MCP traversal results or from a generated `entities.json` artifact
	•	Do not hardcode the full BNY entity list from the README because that list is not fully enumerated there


